          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            Not sure why Bayern fans are so despondent. Top of the league having won all 5 games, conceded just once and haven't looked like dropping a point. It takes time for a new manager to implement their own style and at the moment, the Bayern players are still in Pep mode. While you are winning, there's no problem. Ancelotti is a good coach, let's wait til they face a good team before everybody cries about Pep leaving. The bookies over here have Bayern at 1/18 to win the league with Dortmund nearest challengers at 10/1..... after 5 games! Pep never won the CL despite having the best squad in the competition, there is a reason for that. When Bayern play Atletico, we can make a direct comparison since Atletico are largely unchanged tactically from last season. My guess is the predictability Pep teams have made it relatively simple for Simeone to base a game-plan around, ditto for Wenger. Ancelotti teams have always been able to adapt more-so. Give him time.

            @neumi17 I totally share your opinion about Guardiola's importance for Bayern.
